# Release, handoff, and Live View SOP (agent must follow)

When the user asks for a **shipping build**, **release**, **hotfix binaries**, or **SOP completion**, or when finishing work that affects downloadable binaries or download documentation, do **all** of the following that apply—**without waiting to be reminded**.

## Git (required when code or README download docs change)

1. **`git status`** — ensure no unintended files.
2. **Commit** with a clear message (what changed / why).
3. **`git push`** to the branch the user is using (usually `main` or their stated release branch). If push fails, diagnose (remote, auth) and retry; do not end the task with “you should push.”

## Builds (when user wants new executables or a release-style drop)

1. Run **`dotnet build -c Release`** on the solution before packaging.
2. On **Windows**, run **`.\create-release-package.ps1`** (or the user’s stated stamp flow: shared `-BuildStamp` with **`.\build\build-all.ps1`** per README **Release Build SOP**). Use **`Directory.Build.props`** / script **`Version`** unless the user specifies otherwise.
3. **Icon:** If packaging, icon refresh is covered by `create-release-package.ps1`; otherwise follow **`icon-branding-standard.mdc`** (`warrior_icon.ico`).

## README and links (required when producing a new timestamped package for GitHub Release)

1. Update **`README.md`** **[Latest direct download links](#latest-direct-download-links)** with **verbatim full HTTPS** `https://github.com/devildog5x5/ONVIF-ODM/releases/download/v{version}/…` for **each** platform ZIP that was (or will be) uploaded for that tag and stamp.
2. When **CI artifacts** are the authoritative download (no Release upload yet), update **`README.md`** **Pinned `main` CI build**: run **`dotnet build -c Release`**, run **`.\build\build-all.ps1`** (or **`gh workflow run dotnet.yml --ref main`**), **`gh run watch`** until success, then paste **verbatim** the successful **Actions run URL**, **artifact name** (`ONVIF-ODM-Windows-x64-r{run}-{attempt}`), **inner portable ZIP file names** from the job log (`Created: artifacts/zips/…`), and **commit SHA** (the commit **that run checked out**); refresh **Source / README refreshed** and **Key files** table dates. **Commit and push** the README on `main`. For follow-up **README-only** corrections to the pin table, include **`[skip ci]`** in the commit message so `.github/workflows/dotnet.yml` does not spawn another Windows pack (avoids README/artifact version drift).
3. Update the **build stamp** line, **Latest tagged release line** (if applicable), and **Source / README refreshed** date when those change.
4. If assets are **not** on GitHub yet, state that clearly in README (CI Artifacts / pending upload) and do **not** invent working `releases/download/…` URLs.
5. If **`main` has fixes that are not in the newest Release ZIPs**, README must **not** imply `releases/download/…` is the newest Windows build — keep **[Latest direct download links](#latest-direct-download-links)** honest (**frozen Release** vs **pinned CI**). If a discontinued edition (e.g. WPF) was removed from the repo, **delete its assets** from existing GitHub Releases (`gh release delete-asset …`) so users cannot download obsolete editions.

## Chat handoff (required in the same turn as the work)

### Mandatory — **“New build links”** block (after **every** rebuild)

The maintainer requires a **fresh, copy-paste-ready link section in the chat reply** whenever a **new** Windows portable build exists. **Do not wait for the user to ask.** Use a clear heading (e.g. **### New build links**) and include **all** of the following that apply:

| Required line | Content |
|---------------|---------|
| **Actions run** | Verbatim `https://github.com/devildog5x5/ONVIF-ODM/actions/runs/<id>` (or **Local build** + full path to folder / `.exe` / `.zip` if no CI) |
| **Artifact name** | `ONVIF-ODM-Windows-x64-r{run_number}-{run_attempt}` from CI (from the run’s uploaded artifact) |
| **Inner ZIP** | Exact filename from the job log (`Created: artifacts/zips/OnvifDeviceManager-Avalonia-win-x64-v…zip`) |
| **CLI download** | `gh run download <id> -R devildog5x5/ONVIF-ODM` |

**Rebuild** means: CI **success** after **push** or **`workflow_dispatch`**, or **`.\create-release-package.ps1` / `.\build\build-all.ps1`** producing a new stamped ZIP. If CI is **in progress**, still paste the **run URL** and say **in progress**; when green, provide the **full block** in that turn or the immediate follow-up. **Never** end a rebuild-only turn with “see README” as the only download hint.

1. Paste the **same** URLs into **`README.md` [Pinned `main` CI build](#pinned-main-ci-build-windows-x64-portable)** when CI is the source (per README SOP).
2. When **`main`** CI produced a new Windows portable ZIP after your push, **in the same turn** also **update the README pin** (run URL, artifact name, inner ZIP from job log, commit SHA), refresh **Source / README refreshed**, commit with **`[skip ci]`** for README-only pin commits, and **push**. If your only commits were **`[skip ci]`** README/doc fixes, **no new artifact exists** until **`gh workflow run Build -R devildog5x5/ONVIF-ODM --ref main`** (or **Actions → Build → Run workflow**) and you re-pin after green — still paste the **current** pin links in chat if the user asked for links.
3. End with a short **SOP completion** block: checklist **A–G** from README **“After every new binary build”** — each line **✅** or **N/A** with one phrase.

## Limits (be explicit in chat)

- **GitHub Release upload** and **tag creation** may require **`gh`**, browser, or maintainer credentials. If the agent cannot upload, it still updates README **templates** / pending text, runs local packaging, pushes commits, and gives **exact** filenames and **intended** `releases/download/…` URLs for the user to paste after upload.
- **CI** produces artifacts under **Actions**; paste the workflow URL and artifact naming pattern when that is the authoritative download.

## Live View and snapshot (smoke expectations)

After changes under **Live View**, **LibVLC**, **NativeControlHost**, **manifest**, or **snapshot/HTTP** paths, treat these as **minimum verification** (user or agent on Windows):

| Check | Avalonia (Windows portable) |
|-------|-------------------------------|
| Open device → **Live View** | ✅ |
| **Snapshot** with stream **stopped** (still image updates) | ✅ |
| **Start live** → video plays; **Stop** → clean stop | ✅ |
| Extracted folder keeps **`libvlc`** next to **`OnvifDeviceManager.exe`** | ✅ |

If **embedded video** fails but snapshot works, note **Open externally** / VLC path and any **status text** in the UI.

**Handoff:** Summarize outcomes briefly; do not enumerate routine files for the user to inspect. If something is **high-impact** (security/secrets, data loss, breaking API, wrong version or public download URLs, licensing), call out that item only with a clear **what** and **why**.
